SET content = '[{"type":"schedule","title":"Schedule","rows":[{"time":"11:30","label":"Brunch & kick-off"},{"time":"18:00","label":"Submission deadline"}]},{"type":"markdown","title":"Build directions","body":"The simplest versions are a good warm-up: a bot that gifts a card, or an agent that tops up your eSIM the moment you land. Those are close to what you get the instant you connect, so the builds that stand out *compose* the primitives into something that had to be engineered. Three directions worth chasing:\n\n**Event-driven baskets.** An agent watches a real-world signal and assembles a multi-item order in response, then confirms fulfillment, with no single \"buy this\" command. e.g. a release bot that, when a launch ships, issues a reward bundle to the whole team, picking each person''s local coffee and ride-share brand by country.\n\n**Self-funding agents.** An agent that earns and spends from the same balance under a policy. Affiliate commissions or deposits top it up; the agent spends within caps, autonomously. e.g. a community bot that earns referral commissions on members'' top-ups and recycles them into monthly data for members who can''t afford it. A real economic loop, not just a spender.\n\n**Value routing across borders.** Given an intent and a destination, the agent picks the right instrument (airtime, a local gift card, eSIM data, or a bill payment) across 170+ countries, then settles over Lightning or crypto. e.g. \"Get $40 of value to my brother in Lagos\" and it decides local airtime plus a grocery card beats a US gift card he can''t redeem. The hardest direction: it is an optimization and fulfillment problem, not a lookup."},{"type":"markdown","title":"What you''re working with","body":"Everything Bitrefill sells is purchasable by an agent, and the recommended way to reach it is the Bitrefill eCommerce MCP.\n\n**Products:** gift cards (Amazon, Steam, Netflix, Spotify, and hundreds more), mobile top-ups (airtime and data worldwide), eSIMs (including topping up an existing eSIM by its ICCID), and bill payments. 170+ countries.\n\n**Payment rails:** Bitcoin, Lightning, Ethereum, USDC, USDT, Solana, or your account balance.\n\n**The mechanics that make the interesting builds possible:**\n\n- **Autonomous checkout:** buy paying from `balance` and there is no human in the loop. This is what satisfies the challenge, so wire it up early.\n- **Multi-product orders:** one purchase can contain many products. This is how you build baskets.\n- **Order polling and webhooks:** know the moment an order is delivered, so your agent can react instead of waiting.\n- **Bulk gift-card batches:** issue many cards programmatically for rewards, payouts, or campaigns.\n- **Affiliate commissions:** an agent can earn, not just spend."},{"type":"markdown","title":"Get started","body":"**1. Get a free developer key** at [bitrefill.com/account/developers](https://www.bitrefill.com/account/developers). The key is free; the only thing that can ever cost money is your own model.\n\n**2. Connect over MCP (recommended).** The hosted endpoint is the same for every agent and framework:\n\n```\nhttps://api.bitrefill.com/mcp/<YOUR_KEY>\n```\n\nAdd it as a remote MCP server in your agent. Key-in-URL is best for agents, scripts, and headless runs; OAuth (browser sign-in) also works if you want a human to authorize spend. The MCP exposes the full purchase loop: search products, get details, buy, and check orders.\n\n**3. Follow the official quickstart** for the end-to-end walkthrough and code: [docs.bitrefill.com/docs/quickstart-2](https://docs.bitrefill.com/docs/quickstart-2). Prefer a fully custom build? The REST API is documented at [docs.bitrefill.com/docs/api-overview](https://docs.bitrefill.com/docs/api-overview), but MCP is the fastest path for most teams."},{"type":"markdown","title":"No paid agent plan?","body":"You don''t need a paid agent subscription. The Bitrefill MCP works with almost any agent, and the only cost is the model, so pair it with a free one.\n\n**Already pay for an agent?** Just add the MCP endpoint above to Claude ([Desktop](https://claude.ai/download) or Code), ChatGPT, or [Cursor](https://www.cursor.com) and start building.\n\n**No paid plan? Pick a free agent that speaks MCP:**\n\n- **VS Code + GitHub Copilot** has a genuinely useful free tier with agent mode and MCP support. Setup: [Copilot](https://github.com/features/copilot) and [MCP in VS Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/copilot/chat/mcp-servers).\n- **Gemini CLI** is free with a generous daily quota and supports MCP: [github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli](https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli).\n- **Cline** is a free, open-source VS Code extension where you bring your own model key: [github.com/cline/cline](https://github.com/cline/cline).\n- **Goose** is a free, open-source, model-agnostic agent: [github.com/block/goose](https://github.com/block/goose).\n\n**Then plug in a free model** (for the bring-your-own-key agents):\n\n- **Google AI Studio / Gemini API**, free tier: [aistudio.google.com](https://aistudio.google.com)\n- **OpenRouter**, includes free models: [openrouter.ai](https://openrouter.ai)\n- **Groq**, fast and free to start: [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com)\n- **Local and fully free** via [Ollama](https://ollama.com) or [LM Studio](https://lmstudio.ai)\n\nOne caveat: the buy loop is multi-step tool use, so pick a model with solid tool-calling. Very small local models often struggle with it; a capable free model (for example the Gemini free tier, or a strong OpenRouter free model) will get you through the whole journey."},{"type":"markdown","title":"Test without spending real money","body":"You can build and demo the entire purchase flow without spending real money. There are two test paths, and both return a real redemption code.\n\n**Path A, crypto (no setup):** buy the `test-gift-card-code` product with any crypto method and request the payment link. A link is returned but you never pay it; the test product delivers regardless. Works on any key, today.\n\n**Path B, test credits (account balance):** this proves the real `balance` checkout your app will use. It requires test credits to be provisioned on your account, which are granted manually. **Message a member of the Bitrefill team with your account email address to have them added.** At the event, mentors can do this on the spot.\n\nFull walkthrough, the exact tool calls, the one polling rule that trips everyone up, and a reference run: [read the testing guide](https://github.com/sacha-l/bitrefill-gift-card-concierge/blob/master/TESTING.md)."},{"type":"markdown","title":"Resources","body":"- **Quickstart:** [docs.bitrefill.com/docs/quickstart-2](https://docs.bitrefill.com/docs/quickstart-2)\n- **eCommerce MCP docs:** [docs.bitrefill.com/docs/ecommerce-mcp](https://docs.bitrefill.com/docs/ecommerce-mcp)\n- **Core concepts:** [docs.bitrefill.com/docs/core-concepts](https://docs.bitrefill.com/docs/core-concepts)\n- **Testing guide (test credits + full flow):** [github.com/sacha-l/bitrefill-gift-card-concierge/blob/master/TESTING.md](https://github.com/sacha-l/bitrefill-gift-card-concierge/blob/master/TESTING.md)\n- **Reference app (shop-on-command concierge):** [github.com/sacha-l/bitrefill-gift-card-concierge](https://github.com/sacha-l/bitrefill-gift-card-concierge)\n- **MCP server repo:** [github.com/bitrefill/bitrefill-mcp-server](https://github.com/bitrefill/bitrefill-mcp-server)\n- **Agent skills:** [github.com/bitrefill/agents](https://github.com/bitrefill/agents)\n- **CLI:** [github.com/bitrefill/cli](https://github.com/bitrefill/cli)\n- **awesome-agentic-payments:** [github.com/bitrefill/awesome-agentic-payments](https://github.com/bitrefill/awesome-agentic-payments)\n- **Get a developer key:** [bitrefill.com/account/developers](https://www.bitrefill.com/account/developers)\n- **Agent-readable docs index:** [docs.bitrefill.com/llms.txt](https://docs.bitrefill.com/llms.txt)"},{"type":"markdown","title":"What to submit","body":"To count, a submission needs all of these:\n\n▢ **A working autonomous purchase.** An AI agent that searches, buys, and pays on Bitrefill on its own. The checkout runs without a human clicking pay.\n\n▢ **A landing page if your build is a CLI tool or an app interface.** A single page that explains what it is, what it does, and how to run it, with a link to the demo.\n\n▢ **A video demo link, 4 minutes maximum.** Walk through what the app does from start to finish and show one complete, successful user journey: a real search, buy, pay, and redemption. Anything over 4 minutes won''t be reviewed in full.\n\n▢ **A public GitHub URL** for your code.\n\nSubmit using the button below. See how submissions are scored just below."},{"type":"markdown","title":"How it''s judged","body":"Every submission is scored on three things:\n\n**Use of the Bitrefill tech stack.** How well you put the MCP, API, and products to work.\n\n**Followed the requirements.** A real autonomous purchase, plus everything on the submission checklist.\n\n**Innovation.** How original and interesting the idea is.\n\nThe three scores are averaged into a final score. That ranking picks the prize winners and the top 5 teams we spotlight."},{"type":"markdown","title":"Questions & teammates","body":"Questions, support, and finding a team: join the Telegram at [t.me/joinWebzero](https://t.me/joinWebzero). Drop in before and during the event. On the day, Bitrefill mentors are on hand throughout."},{"type":"markdown","title":"FAQ","body":"**Do I need real crypto to test?** No. Use the crypto test product (no setup) or ask the Bitrefill team for test credits to exercise the account-balance checkout. Neither spends real money.\n\n**Can I use any model or framework?** Yes. Build your agent however you like and connect to Bitrefill over MCP, or use the REST API for a fully custom build.\n\n**I don''t have a paid agent plan. Can I still take part?** Yes. See \"No paid agent plan?\" above for free agents and free models that work with the MCP.\n\n**MCP or REST, which should I pick?** MCP is the fastest path and the recommended default. Use REST when you need full programmatic control over a custom agent.\n\n**Solo or team?** Either works.\n\n**What products and regions are covered?** Gift cards, mobile top-ups, eSIMs, and bill payments across 170+ countries."}]'::jsonb,
    updated_at = NOW()
WHERE slug = 'bitrefill-2026';
